The paper proposes a new algorithm for Sparse Subspace Clustering (SSC) that improves clustering accuracy while maintaining low computational time. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Orthogonal Matching Pursuit (OMP), which is a technique commonly used in signal processing and information theory, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experiments on synthetic data and two real-world databases, indicating that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
